Isko hume 90Â° clockwise ghumana hai.



## Step 1 â€” Transpose

Transpose hum 10th class se jaante hain ðŸ˜„
Row ko column bana do, column ko row.

Transpose ke baad:


1  4  7
2  5  8
3  6  9


Yaha bas itna hua:

> matrix[i][j] â†’ matrix[j][i]



 Step 2 â€” Reverse Rows (sirf rows)

Ab hum har row ko ulta kar dete hain:

1  4  7   â†’   7  4  1
2  5  8   â†’   8  5  2
3  6  9   â†’   9  6  3


Final:

7  4  1
8  5  2
9  6  3


Yahi hai 90Â° clockwise rotation.

So formula ho gaya:

>Transpose + Reverse each row


270Â° rotation (90Â° anti-clockwise)

Bas ek chhota sa twist.

Transpose same rahega,
lekin is baar hum rows nahi, columns value reverse karenge.

Transpose:


1  4  7
2  5  8
3  6  9


Columns value reverse:

3  6  9
2  5  8
1  4  7

Ye hai 270Â° clockwise (ya 90Â° anti-clockwise)

So rule:

> Transpose + Reverse columns

180Â° rotation â€” new trick ðŸ”¥

Ye mera favourite part hai.

180Â° ka matlab:

> image ko bilkul ulta kar dena

Isme transpose ki bhi zarurat nahi hoti.

Bas ye karo:

 Rows reverse karo
 Fir columns reverse karo

Ya ek line me:

matrix[i][j] â†” matrix[n-1-i][n-1-j]

Example:


1 2 3      9 8 7
4 5 6  â†’   6 5 4
7 8 9      3 2 1

Ye hota hai 180Â° rotation.

Aur haan, theoretically tum 90Â° ko do baar call karke bhi 180Â° bana sakte ho,
aur 90Â° ko teen baar call karke 270Â° ðŸ˜‚
lekin corporate me hum aisa nahi karte â€” waha optimized solution chahiye.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Below code for 90 degree clockwise rotation

class Solution {
    public void rotate(int[][] matrix) {
        int n = matrix.length;

        // Step 1: Transpose
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                int temp = matrix[i][j];
                matrix[i][j] = matrix[j][i];
                matrix[j][i] = temp;
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Reverse each row
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n / 2; j++) {
                int temp = matrix[i][j];
                matrix[i][j] = matrix[i][n - j - 1];
                matrix[i][n - j - 1] = temp;
            }
        }

    }
}



